<doc id="424248" wikidata="Q13171513" url="?curid=424248" title="Micromalthidae">
<text>Micromalthidae is an ancient family of small beetles belonging to the suborder Archostemata. The only known living representative is the telephone-pole beetle, &quot;Micromalthus debilis&quot;. A few extinct species have been described, the oldest being the Late Permian &quot;Archaeomalthus synoriacos&quot;. It is one of the oldest families of beetles still existing today.

&quot;Micromalthus debilis&quot; is remarkable for its paedogenetic reproductive strategy which is almost unique in the animal kingdom, with the partial exception of Loricifera, and that could have already evolved in prehistoric Micromalthidae.

